    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="troubleshoot">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, make sure the vehicle batteries are at 75% state of
                        charge (SOC) or higher. This represents an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 12.4 volts. Batteries
                        with an OCV of 12 volts or less are either completely discharged or have a dead cell.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, check any light or indicator lamp filaments that are
                        suspected of being open (burned out). This is done to avoid unnecessary extensive circuit
                        checks.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins,
                        wires, etc. Refer to TEST EQUIPMENT AND CONNECTOR REPAIR section in GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL in the
                        CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the technician determines that a fuse is blown, while checking its condition, he is
                        directed to locate the cause of the overload condition and to repair it. While no further
                        instruction on this procedure is listed in the diagnostic tables, the common procedure is as
                        follows: isolate sections of the circuit, by disconnecting connectors, and measure the
                        resistance to ground to find the circuit that is shorted to ground. Then locate the damaged spot
                        in the wire or connector and repair.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Diagnostics for circuits that are malfunctioning by sticking in the on position are generally
                        not covered in detail. It is assumed that the technician knows to check for a malfunctioning
                        switch, relay, or solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Air Conditioner</title>
            <table id="t0824101" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Air Conditioner</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth=".75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Does heater-A/C blower function properly?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>See
                                    <hotlnk document="s08230_304.xml" xrefid="x0824101">Heater Troubleshooting
                                        Chart</hotlnk>for trouble- shooting of blower system.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (37), move key switch to ignition position, and move blower
                                    switch to low position. At (37), measure voltage from circuit 77 to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(37), 77 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77 or blower switch, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With switches still on, at connector (37), measure voltage from circuit 77 to
                                    77-GA.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(37), 77 to 77-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 77-GA/11-GA/ 11-GF, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Bench test switch (37) by measuring from terminal A to B with switch in on
                                    position.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(37), A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Does A/C switch (37) indicator function?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (41) and reconnect switch (37). With key switch in ignition
                                    position and A/C switch (37) in on position, at (41) circuit 77A, measure voltage to
                                    ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(41), 77A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77A, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Reconnect connector (41) and disconnect (235). Move A/C and key switch to on
                                    position and at manual temp. control switch (235), measure voltage from circuit 77E
                                    to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(235), 77E to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77A or 77E, then repair</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Make sure evaporator is above 3.3&#176;C (38&#176;F) and at the switch side of
                                    (235) measure resistance from terminal 1 to 2 with control at coolest setting.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(235), term 1 to 2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective temperature control switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Reconnect connector (235) and remove A/C relay (72). Move key switch to ignition
                                    position and at relay socket (72) with A/C switch on and cool selected, measure
                                    voltage from circuit 77B to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(72), 77B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Install a test jumper at relay socket (72) from circuit 77B to 77F. Disconnect
                                    circuit 77F at the A/C compressor clutch and move key switch to ignition position.
                                    At circuit 77F, measure voltage to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Near compressor 77F to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77F from A/C relay, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Reconnect circuit 77F to refrigerant compressor clutch. Can clutch be heard
                                    engaging?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective refrigerant compressor clutch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (80) from the high pressure switch safety switch. With A/C
                                    switch on, move key switch to ignition position, and at (80), measure voltage from
                                    circuit 77J to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(80), 77J to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77J, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (74) from the low pressure switch safety switch. With A/C
                                    switch on, move key switch to ignition position, and at (74) measure voltage from
                                    circuit 77H to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(74), 77H to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77H, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>14.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With A/C switch on and temperature switch set to cool, at relay socket (72),
                                    measure voltage from circuit 77B to 77-G.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(72), 77B to 77-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 77-G/11-GE, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>15.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At relay socket (72), measure resistance of circuit 77L.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(72), cavity 4 to 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 77L, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>16.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At (72) install a test jumper from circuit 77B to 77C. Set A/C to cool and key
                                    switch to ignition position and at conn. (80) and circuit 77K, measure voltage to
                                    ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(80), 77K to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77C or 77K, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>17.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With switches still turned on, at conn. (74) circuit 77D, measure voltage to
                                    ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(74), 77D to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>18.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance of low pressure safety switch (74).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Across low pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>If refrigerant charge is within limits, replace defective low pressure switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>19.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance of high pressure safety switch (80).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Across high pressure switch</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>If refrigerant charge is within limits, replace defective high pressure switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>20.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>Bench test A/C relay by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>A/C relay, 30 to 87A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>21.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>Bench test A/C relay by applying +12V to terminal 85 and ground to terminal 86.
                                    Measure resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>Energized A/C relay, 30 to 87.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>22.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>Air conditioner circuits check good. Remove test jumper, re-install relay, and
                                    reconnect the separated connectors.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
